  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Caroline Weston describes the details of her illness. She writes: &quot;Everyone is sick here there are two or three in every house &amp; in some families all.&quot; She begs Deborah to be careful. She has heard from Anne [Warren Weston] that cousin Mary Arnold is very ill and fears that &quot;Grandmas folks will get sick taking care of her.&quot; She emphasizes the kindness shown to Caroline Weston by Mrs. Moorfield. &quot;My young Ladies have gone without me.&quot; [The &quot;young ladies&quot; are probably Caroline&apos;s pupils.]</subfield>
